The SMG fraction ($f_{\rm OIRTC}$) shown in \autoref{colorhist} represents the fractional number density in each color bin, and its calculation takes color errors into account, as the uncertainties of $f_{\rm OIRTC}$ are obtained through Monte Carlo simulations. By describing $f_{\rm OIRTC}$ with model functions and calibrating the training set with those models, it is possible to determine cuts in a quantitative way. 

We therefore first model $f_{\rm OIRTC}$ as a function of color by fitting a functional form, parametrized as
$ 1/(a + e^{-b(x-c)}) $, in which $x$ is the corresponding color. The parametrisation is similar to the Fermi--Dirac distribution, which provides an appropriate description to the distribution of the measured $f_{\rm OIRTC}$, where the fraction on both sides of the color space converge, 
